# CLAUDE.md

This file provides guidance to Claude Code when working with Jac code in this project.

## CRITICAL: Always Validate

After writing or modifying ANY `.jac` or `.cl.jac` file, run:
```bash
{{JAC_BINARY}} check main.jac
```
If errors are reported, fix them before finishing your turn. Do NOT present code to the user without validating first.

## MCP Tools Available

You have access to `jac mcp` tools via the configured MCP server. Use them:
- `validate_jac(code)` — Full type-check + compile validation. MANDATORY after every code change.
- `check_syntax(code)` — Quick parse check while iterating.
- `explain_error(error_message)` — Get fix suggestions for compiler errors.
- `search_docs(query)` — Search official Jac documentation. **Never guess syntax — search first.**
- `format_jac(code)` — Auto-format to standard Jac style.
- `py_to_jac(python_code)` — Transpile Python to Jac.
- `list_examples(category?)` — List available example categories.
- `get_example(name)` — Get working `.jac` files from an example category.

